qa: Make rustfmt happy

doc: Update comparison, readme

Genlop seems to have slowed down significantly ?
qa: Bump MSRV for the CI too
build: Make cargo publish happy
test: Fix history benchmark

qa: Fix redundant `use`s

Rustc beta/nightly added some warnings.

bench: Turn exec_compare's `-p` into a positional argument

Just a bit more practical.

bench: Add a "last sync" case

Will add it to the benchmark doc, kinda to replace teh removed `tgcc` but also because it seems like
a useful example command.  Had to add a sync as the last event of bench/emerge.log so that qlop's
`-l` option does something interesting. Genlop doesn't have a comparable flag, so using `--date`
will have to do.

cli: Bring back `--resume=auto`, rename `any` to `either`

Seemed unnecessary and inconsistent to not have an `auto`.

cli: Harmonize `--color` and `--output` values

Trying to make things a bit more coherent, but this is subjective.

bench: Remove tgcc for genlop

Because genlop doesn't really support that.
bench: Fix stdcomp.sh

bench: Disable emlop config by default

To avoid surprises with configs that cause more work. Added the `start` bench, which shows that the
actual loading of the config file takes negligible time (<1ms), so disabling load in benchmarks
isn't unfair.

deps: Update env_logger

We already depend on anstyle/anstream, so we might as well enable color.

deps: Bump MSRV and emlop version

Newer env_logger needs rust 1.71, which is now the oldest in portage.

doc: Update demos, changelog, readme, etc

* demo.md replaced by demo.sh
* new config screencast

conf: Make `--output` configurable

Same motivation as `--color`.
conf: Fix `--color` parse error string
cli: Remove unneeded hide_possible_values call

cli: Move `--duration` before `--date`

So that `--utc` is right after `--date`.

conf: Make `--color` configurable

Because I felt the need to discreetely force-enable colors for the sreencast. As a result, I need to
bring back an explicit "auto" variant. But renamed the variants to be more straightforward.

Quite happy with ArgParse here, as I can parse into a bool directly, without an enum in between and
handling the isterm logic during parsing.

stats: Shorten table header

`(un)merge count` -> `(un)merges` seems clear enough and makes the columns less needlessly wide.

predict: Find the currently-emerging pkg using emerge's sandbox process commandline

This should be a bit more reliable than looking at the emerge logs since the oldest emerge
process. See bugs 5 and 45 for failure examples. Will need to play with this code for a while to
make sure it behaves as we want. Genlop and qlop use a similar technique, but they don't handle as
many cases and don't seem to have a fallback.
qa: Move proces module to parse/, tweak uses

predict: Refactor how we gather info from processes

* Move some logic from commands.rs to parse/current.rs
* Shorten the emerge commandline shown to the user (hide python interpreter)
* Allow filtering on multiple process names (unused in this commit)
* Renames and cleanups

This works towards getting more information from currently running emerge processes, in particular
getting the actual current ebuild (see bugs 5 and 45). The neater commandline output is just a
drive-by cherry-on-top.
parse: Debug-log the resume list

table: Fix overwide columns when `--last` is used

By checking the widths at flush time instead of insert time. Surprisingly looks like it's a tiny bit
faster, but it's within error margin.

Fixes #42
